  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All integration tests pass</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Status updates delivered within 1 second</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Reconnection handles gracefully</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Redis failures don't crash the service</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Polling fallback works correctly</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    SSE uses fetch + ReadableStream in the client (NOT EventSource) because
    EventSource cannot send Authorization headers. The SSE endpoint must send
    current status on connection before streaming updates.
  </notes>

